    <methods>
      <methodStep>
        <description>
          <para>d13C and d15N stable isotopic signatures were obtained from macrofossils of sawgrass (Cladium jamaicense) at specific depth intervals from a short soil core.  Seeds were collected from macrofossil analyses (seed ST_SS_Saunders_003) of soil cores.  Seeds were inspected under a dissecting microscope and cleaned of rootlets and organic debris.  Seeds were rinsed with DI water and oven dried at 80 degrees C.  Dry seeds were analyzed for 15N and 13C at the SERC Stable Isotope Laboratory at Florida International University using standard elemental analyzer isotope ratio mass spectrometer (EA-IRMS) procedures. Standards are Peedee Belemnite (PDB) for carbon and air (AIR) for nitrogen.</para>
        </description>
        <instrumentation>sieves (1000 micron and 500 micron openings)</instrumentation>
        <instrumentation>30x monocular lens microscopes</instrumentation>
        <instrumentation>65x dissecting microscopes</instrumentation>
        <instrumentation>fine foreceps</instrumentation>
        <instrumentation>balance</instrumentation>
